This paper deals with algorithms for matching user tracks to paths in a road network, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of location data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the databases (cs.DB) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes two methods for solving the multi-track map matching problem, which involves graph-based algorithms and iterative projection schemes, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), or graph theory (cs.GR) sub-categories.
